hLevel': 'none', 'matchedWords': []}, 'residencyProgramSize': {'value': '0', 'matchLevel': 'none', 'matchedWords': []}, 'summary': {'value': 'Midwestern University (MWU) is offering a one-year rotating internship in small animal medicine and surgery. The program is designed to develop the clinical skills of a veterinarian in preparation for the intellectual rigors of a residency or a career in advanced primary care. The Midwestern University Companion Animal Clinic is a modern and innovative veterinary hospital for small animals comprising a 110,000 sq. foot state-of-the-art hospital. 

